A 12-year-old boy's body was discovered at a local train station on Friday. CAPE TOWN - Authorities in the Western Cape are investigating the circumstances around the murder of a boy in Bonteheuwel.The 12-year-old's body was discovered at the local train station on Friday, his hands and feet had been bound.The victim's name has not yet been released, but it s understood he was a grade five pupil at Bramble Way Primary School.Bonteheuwel ward councillor Angus McKenzie says the child was last seen playing in the road. Despite efforts by the community to put a stop to this, the number of kids dying is alarming and should be a warning to everyone. (Edited by Shimoney Regter)